  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "Per the Kubernetes design, IPs should be shared between containers within a pod. However, to accomplish this, Docker must be instructed to use `container` networking when starting the containers [reference](https://docs.docker.com/reference/run/#network-settings). This configuration appears to be missing from the Kubulet code:\n\nhttps://github.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/kubernetes/blob/master/pkg/kubelet/kubelet.go#L307\n\nAs a result, it would appear that IPs will be assigned per container based on the external bridge specified to the Docker daemon arguments.\n",
